r cinema seemed so utterly atrocious to him; strange, foreign—yes, but … atrocious? Let us try to explain it by the German plebeian’s backwardness. The German peasant is old-fashioned and prudish; just try, one day, to walk through a village in nothing but swimming trunks. I have tried, so I know what happens; the men stand stock-still, the women titter, hiding their faces, quite like parlor maids in old-world comedies.

